---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Geometric Series — Hayaan Dangra"
  description="Watch (1/2)^n converge to 1 — add terms one at a time and see each slice fill in a square until it's almost complete."
>
  <section class="demo-page section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Geometric Series: (½)ⁿ</h1>

      <div class="explanation">
        <p>This came from a math class argument. Someone said "you can add an infinite number of things together and get a finite answer" and I said that didn't make sense. Like, doesn't adding forever mean the sum keeps growing forever?</p>
        <p>Turns out no, and this is why: each term is half the previous one. (1/2) + (1/4) + (1/8)... the pieces get small so fast that they never quite fill up the whole square, but they get infinitely close to it.</p>
        <p>The slider adds one term at a time. Watch the remaining gray gap — it always cuts in half. By term 6 you've got 63/64 of the square filled. You'll never finish, but you can get as close as you want.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-container">
        <h2>Fill the Square</h2>
        <canvas id="seriesCanvas" role="img" aria-label="Interactive geometric series visualization — use the slider to add terms and watch the square fill up"></canvas>

        <div class="sum-display">
          <div class="sum-row">
            <span class="sum-label">Sum so far:</span>
            <span class="sum-value"><span id="sumDecimal">0.0000</span> <span class="sum-fraction" id="sumFraction">(0/1)</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="sum-row">
            <span class="sum-label">Terms added:</span>
            <span class="sum-value" id="termsAdded">0 of 6</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sum-row">
            <span class="sum-label">Remaining:</span>
            <span class="sum-value" id="remaining">1.0000</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="controls">
          <div class="control-group">
            <label for="termsSlider">
              Terms: <span id="termsValue">0</span> of 6
            </label>
            <input type="range" id="termsSlider" min="0" max="6" step="1" value="0">
          </div>

          <div class="button-group">
            <button id="addNextBtn">Add Next Term</button>
            <button id="resetBtn">Reset</button>
            <button id="showAllBtn">Show All</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-matters">
        <h2>The Infinite Sum That Equals 1</h2>
        <p>The formal answer is a/(1-r) where r is the ratio between terms. Here r = 1/2, so the sum is (1/2)/(1 - 1/2) = 1. That formula comes from the formula for geometric series, and once you understand it visually, it's obvious why it works.</p>
        <p>This shows up in probability (the chance of eventually winning a game), in computing (binary fractions, like how 0.1111... in binary equals 1), and in calculus as the first example of a convergent infinite series. Every calculus class uses this series to build intuition for convergence before getting into the harder stuff.</p>
        <p>I keep thinking about what "approaching but never reaching" actually means. The sum never equals 1 at a finite step. But the limit is exactly 1. That's the thing I'm still sitting with.</p>
      </div>

      <nav class="demo-nav">
        <a href="/math-explorations/bisector">← Perpendicular Bisector</a>
        <a href="/math-explorations/taylor-series">Next: Taylor Series →</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .demo-page {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-3xl);
  }

  h1 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .explanation {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-2xl);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--green);
  }

  .demo-container {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  canvas {
    width: 100%;
    height: 280px;
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    display: block;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    canvas {
      height: 400px;
    }
  }

  .sum-display {
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .sum-display {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }

  .sum-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .sum-row:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .sum-label {
    color: var(--charcoal);
    min-width: 110px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .sum-label {
      min-width: 130px;
    }
  }

  .sum-value {
    color: #1E7A48;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .sum-fraction {
    color: var(--charcoal);
    font-weight: 400;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .controls {
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .control-group {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  label {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  #termsValue {
    color: #1E7A48;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  input[type="range"] {
    width: 100%;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--mid-gray);
    outline: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--green);
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--green);
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
  }

  .button-group {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  button {
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 44px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .button-group {
      flex-direction: row;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    button {
      width: auto;
      min-width: 120px;
    }
  }

  #addNextBtn {
    background-color: var(--green);
  }

  #addNextBtn:hover {
    background-color: #1E8449;
  }

  .why-matters {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: var(--space-2xl) auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--orange);
  }

  .demo-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .demo-nav {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }

  .demo-nav a {
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    * { animation: none !important; transition: none !important; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const canvas = document.getElementById('seriesCanvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const termsSlider = document.getElementById('termsSlider') as HTMLInputElement;
  const termsValue = document.getElementById('termsValue') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const addNextBtn = document.getElementById('addNextBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const showAllBtn = document.getElementById('showAllBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const sumDecimal = document.getElementById('sumDecimal') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const sumFraction = document.getElementById('sumFraction') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const termsAdded = document.getElementById('termsAdded') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const remaining = document.getElementById('remaining') as HTMLSpanElement;

  const COLORS = [
    '#3498DB', // term 1 — blue
    '#27AE60', // term 2 — green
    '#E67E22', // term 3 — orange
    '#9B59B6', // term 4 — purple
    '#E74C3C', // term 5 — red
    '#3498DB', // term 6 — blue again
  ];

  const LABELS = ['1/2', '1/4', '1/8', '1/16', '1/32', '1/64'];
  const MAX_TERMS = 6;

  function setupCanvas(c: HTMLCanvasElement) {
    const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;
    const rect = c.getBoundingClientRect();
    c.width = rect.width * dpr;
    c.height = rect.height * dpr;
    const ctx = c.getContext('2d')!;
    ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);
    return { ctx, width: rect.width, height: rect.height };
  }

  interface Rect {
    x: number;
    y: number;
    w: number;
    h: number;
    label: string;
    color: string;
  }

  function computeRects(sqX: number, sqY: number, sqW: number, sqH: number): Rect[] {
    const rects: Rect[] = [];

    // Track the remaining unfilled region as we subdivide
    // Each step alternates: even index (0,2,4) = split left half; odd index (1,3,5) = split top half
    // Remaining region tracked as (rx, ry, rw, rh)
    let rx = sqX;
    let ry = sqY;
    let rw = sqW;
    let rh = sqH;

    for (let i = 0; i < MAX_TERMS; i++) {
      let rectX: number, rectY: number, rectW: number, rectH: number;

      if (i % 2 === 0) {
        // Split left half of remaining region
        rectX = rx;
        rectY = ry;
        rectW = rw / 2;
        rectH = rh;
        // Remaining: right half
        rx = rx + rw / 2;
        rw = rw / 2;
      } else {
        // Split top half of remaining region
        rectX = rx;
        rectY = ry;
        rectW = rw;
        rectH = rh / 2;
        // Remaining: bottom half
        ry = ry + rh / 2;
        rh = rh / 2;
      }

      rects.push({
        x: rectX,
        y: rectY,
        w: rectW,
        h: rectH,
        label: LABELS[i],
        color: COLORS[i],
      });
    }

    return rects;
  }

  function drawSeries(n: number) {
    const { ctx, width, height } = setupCanvas(canvas);

    // Clear
    ctx.fillStyle = '#FFFFFF';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);

    // Square dimensions — leave room for padding
    const padding = 20;
    const size = Math.min(width - padding * 2, height - padding * 2, 300);
    const sqX = Math.floor((width - size) / 2);
    const sqY = Math.floor((height - size) / 2);
    const sqW = size;
    const sqH = size;

    const rects = computeRects(sqX, sqY, sqW, sqH);

    // Draw unfilled remainder (full square first, then overlay filled rects)
    ctx.fillStyle = '#ECF0F1';
    ctx.fillRect(sqX, sqY, sqW, sqH);

    // Draw filled rectangles for terms 0..n-1
    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
      const r = rects[i];
      ctx.fillStyle = r.color;
      ctx.fillRect(r.x, r.y, r.w, r.h);

      // Label — only if min dimension >= 30px
      const minDim = Math.min(r.w, r.h);
      if (minDim >= 30) {
        ctx.fillStyle = '#FFFFFF';
        ctx.font = `bold ${Math.max(13, Math.min(16, Math.floor(minDim * 0.22)))}px DM Sans, sans-serif`;
        ctx.textAlign = 'center';
        ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';
        ctx.fillText(r.label, r.x + r.w / 2, r.y + r.h / 2);
      }
    }

    // Square border
    ctx.strokeStyle = '#2C3E50';
    ctx.lineWidth = 2;
    ctx.strokeRect(sqX, sqY, sqW, sqH);

    // Reset text alignment
    ctx.textAlign = 'left';
    ctx.textBaseline = 'alphabetic';
  }

  function updateDisplay(n: number) {
    // S_N = 1 - (1/2)^N
    // Exact fraction: numerator = 2^N - 1, denominator = 2^N
    const denom = Math.pow(2, n);
    const numer = denom - 1;
    const sumVal = n === 0 ? 0 : numer / denom;
    const remainVal = 1 - sumVal;

    termsValue.textContent = String(n);
    sumDecimal.textContent = sumVal.toFixed(4);

    if (n === 0) {
      sumFraction.textContent = '(0/1)';
    } else {
      sumFraction.textContent = `(${numer}/${denom})`;
    }

    termsAdded.textContent = `${n} of ${MAX_TERMS}`;
    remaining.textContent = remainVal.toFixed(4);
  }

  function update() {
    const n = parseInt(termsSlider.value, 10);
    drawSeries(n);
    updateDisplay(n);

    // Disable Add Next if at max
    addNextBtn.disabled = n >= MAX_TERMS;
    addNextBtn.style.opacity = n >= MAX_TERMS ? '0.5' : '1';
  }

  termsSlider.addEventListener('input', update);

  addNextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const n = parseInt(termsSlider.value, 10);
    if (n < MAX_TERMS) {
      termsSlider.value = String(n + 1);
      update();
    }
  });

  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    termsSlider.value = '0';
    update();
  });

  showAllBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    termsSlider.value = String(MAX_TERMS);
    update();
  });

  const handleResize = () => { update(); };
  window.addEventListener('resize', handleResize);
  document.addEventListener('astro:before-swap', () => {
    window.removeEventListener('resize', handleResize);
  });

  // Initial draw
  update();
</script>
